results.lead_paragraph: As was expected from the outset, the latest Soviet venture into space achieved spectacular results. Lieut.-Col. Bykovsky set a new record of 82 orbits around the earth. Valentina Tereshkova became the first woman in space and at the same time more than doubled the largest number of orbits made so far by an American, a total of 49 to Major Cooper's 22.
